I would like to hear some responses from users of Warp in the corporate arena.
I really am not very interested in what college students think about the
marketability of Warp, how it stacks up against Windows 95, or how the games
play under it. This is of little to no import to me.

I am a software developer at a LARGE computer firm and we are trying to
port our existing Windows application over to OS/2. We are not doing this
because we have a group of OS/2 fanatics in house. We are doing this
because our customers, our corporate customers in the fortune 100, are
demanding better performance, features, and connectivity to their legacy
systems.

I will most likely get flamed for this post but that is the nature of this
forum. To expound on ideas and make judgements about the usability of IBM
OS/2 Warp (and beyond). I have only recently joined this newsgroup and I
see a disturbing number of messages that lead nowhere in their banter aside
from taking shots at each other and at other systems.

We have Nt and Windows 95 in house. We are developing for them too. Unlike
the majority of "fanatics" of a given platform, we follow what our customers
want, not what the trade press, internal systems analysts, or even management
wants.

Just my two cents.

-Marc

