I don't know if I count as corporate, but here goes.

I'm the network analyst for a 150-node Novell network at the University of
Illinois, Urbana-Champaign. I hate Windows. When users push me to add 
Windows to their desktop, I do it, but only then. I love OS/2.
What I want are apps for OS/2. Ain't none worth buying. So we use OS/2 to
multi-task DOS apps, which it does very well. But I don't want to multi-task
DOS apps. What I *want* to do is format every drive HPFS, run Warp v3.0 and
native OS/2 apps for productivity. I want to be able to do drag and drop 
mail merges so I don't have to spend time teaching secretaries how to build
the damn things in a DOS/Win app. I want my users to be able to move between
tasks without having to worry about a GPF, UAE, or any other damn thing.
If you can get me decent apps at a decent price, you've got my money.
If you give me a mediocre app at an outrageous price, I'll just muddle along
with what I've got, thank you.

Steve
